===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[advocatus diaboli]]'', "devil’s advocate"

===Idiomatic noun===
'''devil’s advocate'''
#One who [[debate]]s from a view which they may not actually hold, usually to determine its [[validity]], or simply for the sake of [[argument]].
#(''Roman Catholic Church'') A [[canon]] lawyer appointed by the [[Church]] to argue against the canonization of the proposed [[candidate]].
